            Whether you manage a local solar upgrade scheme, a government housing initiative, or a solar-powered transport hub, PV Industries is equipped to handle your solar waste stream from collection through to final recycling and reporting.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- Government Solutions Section -->
    <section class="government-solutions-section">
      <div class="container">
        <div class="solutions-content">
          <h2 class="solutions-title">Comprehensive Government Solutions</h2>

          <div class="solutions-grid">
            <!-- Local Councils Column -->
            <div class="solution-column councils-column">
              <div class="column-header">
                <div class="header-icon">
                  <svg width="32" height="32" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none">
                    <path d="M3 21V7L12 3L21 7V21M3 21L12 13M3 21H21M21 21L12 13M12 13V21" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2"/>
                  </svg>
                </div>
                <h3 class="column-title">Working with Local Councils</h3>
              </div>

              <div class="solution-features">
                <h4>Services Include:</h4>
                <ul class="features-list">
                  <li>Bulk solar panel pickup and disposal from transfer stations or depots</li>
                  <li>End-of-life system collection from public buildings and facilities</li>
                  <li>Drop-off and collection programs for residents (community recycling programs)</li>
                  <li>Reporting on waste diversion rates for council sustainability reporting</li>
                  <li>Public education support, such as materials and signage for solar waste disposal areas</li>
                </ul>

                <div class="solution-highlight">
                  <h4>Planning a council-wide solar upgrade or clean-out?</h4>
                  <p>Let us manage the end-of-life process and reduce long-term disposal costs.</p>
                </div>
              </div>
            </div>

            <!-- State & Federal Agencies Column -->
            <div class="solution-column agencies-column">
              <div class="column-header">
                <div class="header-icon">
                  <svg width="32" height="32" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none">
                    <path d="M12 2L2 7L12 12L22 7L12 2Z" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2"/>
                    <path d="M2 17L12 22L22 17" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2"/>
